<typeStatus id="592CF9F9FFBB8508FEF0F99CFE0FF9E0" box="[350,448,1634,1660]" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FE5FF99CFCEBF9E0" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." box="[497,804,1634,1660]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lonchophyllus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FE5FF99CFCEBF9E0" box="[497,804,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">Myoxanthus lonchophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lost, and the species is here lectotypified using an illustration associated with the original material. The species, like its relatives 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FC49F979FB73F93C" authorityName="Frey &amp; Sanson" authorityYear="2006" box="[999,1212,1671,1696]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conceicionensis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FC49F979FB73F93C" box="[999,1212,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. conceicionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FB66F979FA96F93C" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1224,1369,1671,1696]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FB66F979FA96F93C" box="[1224,1369,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FA23F979FF19F958" authorityName="Fraga &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2003" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FA23F979FF19F958" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. ruschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is endemic to southern 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFBB8508FE4DF954FDE4F958" box="[483,555,1706,1732]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. They share the fleshy flowers frequently mottled or dotted with dark purple-red, petals with margins revolute, a fleshy lip with apical margins revolute, column with a pair of calli on the column foot and anther cap ciliate-fimbriate. However, 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FDCDF90DFCEBF890" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." box="[611,804,1778,1804]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lonchophyllus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FDCDF90DFCEBF890" box="[611,804,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. lonchophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized by the conspicuous fimbriate margins of the lip. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FF52F8E8FE15F8AC" authorityName="Fraga &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2003" box="[252,474,1814,1840]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FF52F8E8FE15F8AC" box="[252,474,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">Myoxanthus ruschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a ciliate to fimbriate lip, but only apically, and the petals are not revolute. The lip of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FF65F8C5FE92F8C8" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[203,349,1851,1876]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FF65F8C5FE92F8C8" box="[203,349,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may also have short fimbriate margins, but it is fleshier with the apex rounded.
</paragraph>
